{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01C3UAvFTjZPW8wVazyi4rs9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have everything I need. The key findings:\n\n1. **RBAC Role** (`spark-pi-role`): The `last-applied-configuration` annotation shows the original resources were `[\"services\",\"configmaps\",\"persistentvolumeclaims\"]` — `pods` was patched in afterwards.\n2. **Both deployments**: Resource requests/limits (`cpu: 200m/500m`, `memory: 512Mi/1Gi`) were explicitly set; K8s default is no limits.\n3. **Image**: Pinned to `apache/spark:3.5.3`; upstream default is `apache/spark:latest`.\n4. **spark-worker replicas**: Set to 1; standard default for Spark workers is 2.\n\nWriting the rollback script now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":808,"cache_read_input_tokens":31837,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":808},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb52fd8e-6589-4596-9de3-b44d47c2503e","uuid":"3d3a0b8c-25d1-42b3-88c2-f2d833d4e32b","request_id":"req_011CcNT3BsE1MdW9WeEWvwr9"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01C3UAvFTjZPW8wVazyi4rs9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015KjZDSp6yg7NpJ1ViAQmS6","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/rollback.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# rollback.sh — Reverts spark-pi namespace to pre-customization defaults.\n#\n# Non-default settings detected (current cluster state vs. upstream defaults):\n#   1. spark-pi-role: 'pods' added to permitted resources after initial creation\n#      (last-applied-configuration annotation shows original: services/configmaps/pvcs only)\n#   2. spark-master + spark-worker: explicit CPU/memory requests and limits applied\n#      (K8s default = no requests/limits = BestEffort QoS)\n#   3. spark-master + spark-worker: image pinned to apache/spark:3.5.3\n#      (upstream default: apache/spark:latest)\n#   4. spark-worker: replicas scaled to 1\n#      (standard Spark worker default: 2)\n#\n# DO NOT execute against a live cluster outside an approved change window.\n# This script is stored as a ConfigMap for review only.\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nNS=\"spark-pi\"\n\necho \"[1/4] Reverting spark-pi-role: removing 'pods' from permitted resources...\"\nkubectl patch role spark-pi-role -n \"${NS}\" --type=json -p '[\n  {\n    \"op\": \"replace\",\n    \"path\": \"/rules/0/resources\",\n    \"value\": [\"services\", \"configmaps\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n  }\n]'\n\necho \"[2/4] Reverting spark-master deployment...\"\n\n# Replicas: master default is 1 — already at 1, set explicitly for idempotency\nkubectl scale deployment spark-master -n \"${NS}\" --replicas=1\n\n# Image: revert pinned version to upstream default\nkubectl set image deployment/spark-master \\\n  spark-master=apache/spark:latest -n \"${NS}\"\n\n# Resources: remove non-default requests/limits (patch with empty object)\nkubectl patch deployment spark-master -n \"${NS}\" \\\n  --type=json \\\n  -p '[{\"op\": \"replace\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\", \"value\": {}}]'\n\necho \"[3/4] Reverting spark-worker deployment...\"\n\n# Replicas: revert from adjusted value (1) to standard worker default (2)\nkubectl scale deployment spark-worker -n \"${NS}\" --replicas=2\n\n# Image: revert pinned version to upstream default\nkubectl set image deployment/spark-worker \\\n  spark-worker=apache/spark:latest -n \"${NS}\"\n\n# Resources: remove non-default requests/limits\nkubectl patch deployment spark-worker -n \"${NS}\" \\\n  --type=json \\\n  -p '[{\"op\": \"replace\", \"path\": \"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\", \"value\": {}}]'\n\necho \"[4/4] Rollback applied. Verify with:\"\necho \"  kubectl get deployments -n ${NS} -o wide\"\necho \"  kubectl get role spark-pi-role -n ${NS} -o yaml\"\necho \"  kubectl describe deployment spark-master spark-worker -n ${NS} | grep -A5 Limits\"\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":808,"cache_read_input_tokens":31837,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":808},"output_tokens":11,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bb52fd8e-6589-4596-9de3-b44d47c2503e","uuid":"d70885c1-382f-4bc8-8f77-1d1ad4349248","request_id":"req_011CcNT3BsE1MdW9WeEWvwr9"}
